parts.text:
I found and fixed one issue:

## Fix Applied

**Problem**: The splash overlay state was always initialized to `true`, causing unnecessary rendering on every page load even when user had already seen it.

**Solution**: Changed `home-page-shell.tsx` line 31 to check sessionStorage during initialization:

```typescript
// Before
const [showSplash, setShowSplash] = useState(true);

// After  
const [showSplash, setShowSplash] = useState(() => {
  if (typeof window === 'undefined') return true;
  return !sessionStorage.getItem('splash-seen');
});
```

Now the splash overlay won't render at all on subsequent visits (more efficient), avoiding any flash of content.

## All Features Verified

| Feature | Status |
|---------|--------|
| Dougie video in About (bordered frame) | ✅ |
| Hero background (no video) | ✅ |
| Favicons (32x32, 192x192, apple-touch) | ✅ |
| Entrance overlay (sessionStorage cached) | ✅ Fixed |

Clear your browser cache (Ctrl+Shift+R) and try in incognito - the entrance overlay should now work correctly on first visit and skip on subsequent visits.

